owd, who have not had a great time of it on the track so far: still medal-less in the athletics.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Italians next to me are standing up clapping because Pietro Arese has snuck into the final in sixth.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3402, \"end\": 3410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9996797971765913, \"rank\": 0.00031998287927849817, \"text\": \"Italians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the front, Jakob Ingebrigtsen and Josh Kerr cross practically together to qualify for Tuesday's final with ease.\", \"from\": 3504, \"to\": 3619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3518, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 3541, \"end\": 3545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"score\": 0.6301518109415842, \"rank\": 0.5677797379601651, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"George Mills, son of England full-back Danny, is run out of it in 11th: he had to run in the repechage so you can forgive a little tiredness.\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3642, \"end\": 3649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.711310979933824, \"rank\": 0.38975213595024477, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a high jump final going on, although someone should tell world record holder Yaroslava Mahuchikh.\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3850, \"end\": 3869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yaroslava Mahuchikh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is in a battle for gold with Nicola Olyslagers of Australia, but is currently asleep on the infield in a sleeping bag.\", \"from\": 3872, \"to\": 3994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3905, \"end\": 3911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9987689546917253, \"rank\": 0.0012325626488543296, \"text\": \"Nicola\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 3926, \"end\": 3935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9347253576020667, \"rank\": 0.06283071306644328, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What the actual.\", \"from\": 3995, \"to\": 4011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson looks like she has GEARS.\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4013, \"end\": 4023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9996488184137353, \"rank\": 0.00035130495842503994, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wins her semi-final at a canter, easing down at the end but still registering the fastest time of the round.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She will run for gold at 8.47pm tomorrow night.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As cool as you like from Hodgkinson.\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4235, \"end\": 4245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9996488184137353, \"rank\": 0.00035130495842503994, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She controlled the race from the start before turning on the afterburners down the home straight.\", \"from\": 4247, \"to\": 4344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Same again tomorrow night, please\\u2026  Not a great start to the 800m semi-finals for Great Britain: Phoebe Gill finished fourth in the first one and is already out of the fastest loser spots, and Jemma Reekie never got into them, finishing fifth.\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4427, \"end\": 4440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999534607338818, \"rank\": 4.6498264394750005e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4442, \"end\": 4448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Buffay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.572341382696345e-15, \"text\": \"Phoebe\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Buffay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Buffay\"}, {\"begin\": 4538, \"end\": 4550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jemma_Reekie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jemma Reekie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jemma_Reekie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jemma_Reekie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost everyone in front of her ran a PB, to be fair.\", \"from\": 4589, \"to\": 4642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4627, \"end\": 4629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.3333118225807537e-12, \"text\": \"PB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keely Hodgkinson to come in the third semi-final, the odds-on favourite for the gold medal in lifetime best form this year.\", \"from\": 4644, \"to\": 4767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4644, \"end\": 4660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her biggest rival for the medal, Mary Moraa of Kenya, is already through.\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4802, \"end\": 4806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.8117975556778763, \"rank\": 0.20690552224190703, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 4816, \"end\": 4821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999820585016705, \"rank\": 1.791366341314205e-05, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty enters his latest hiatus with a scorching warning to anti-doping agencies to root out the cheats.\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 4952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4844, \"end\": 4854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The three-time Olympic champion was part of the men's 4x100m medley relay team which finished fourth in a race won by China.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5008, \"end\": 5027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.14069432262704e-14, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5072, \"end\": 5077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9903928955091118, \"rank\": 0.006128079797699984, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Chinese team were Qin Haiyang and Sun Jiajun, both of whom had tested positive for trimetazidine ahead of the Tokyo Olympics, only to escape sanction from Chinada (the Chinese anti-doping agency).\", \"from\": 5080, \"to\": 5283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"score\": 0.9973156690618799, \"rank\": 0.0025118725284405917, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\"}, {\"begin\": 5105, \"end\": 5116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"score\": 0.9999938624993854, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qin Haiyang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\"}, {\"begin\": 5121, \"end\": 5124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"score\": 0.9848725495873176, \"rank\": 0.014766106821892482, \"text\": \"Sun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\"}, {\"begin\": 5125, \"end\": 5131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\", \"score\": 0.8020135056820301, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jiajun\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\"}, {\"begin\": 5255, \"end\": 5262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"score\": 0.9973156690618799, \"rank\": 0.0025118725284405917, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The agency concluded that the readings were caused by \\\"an isolated mass incident caused by athletes' unknowing consumption of food contaminated with TMZ,\\\" and \\\"no fault or negligence\\\".\", \"from\": 5285, \"to\": 5469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada) had previously confirmed toThe New York Timesthat three Chinese swimmers had previously tested positive for 'trace amounts' of banned drug clenbuterol - with a later anti-doping report naming Qin as one of the three swimmers.\", \"from\": 5471, \"to\": 5728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5471, \"end\": 5502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 5471, \"end\": 5502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 5559, \"end\": 5566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"score\": 0.9973156690618799, \"rank\": 0.0025118725284405917, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_people\"}, {\"begin\": 5695, \"end\": 5698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Shi_Huang\", \"score\": 0.6491100338849392, \"rank\": 0.5020654516257863, \"text\": \"Qin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Shi_Huang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Shi_Huang\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Peaty, who finished fourth alongside Oliver Morgan, Duncan Scott, and Matt Richards, believes swimmers who have been found to have been contaminated on more than one occasion should be banned from the sport for good.\", \"from\": 5730, \"to\": 5950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5771, \"end\": 5784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_Morgan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oliver Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_Morgan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_Morgan\"}, {\"begin\": 5786, \"end\": 5798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362712081, \"rank\": 0.004373974849646029, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 5804, \"end\": 5817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"score\": 0.8167390230818359, \"rank\": 0.2243767313019458, \"text\": \"Matt Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"One of my favourite quotes I have seen lately is 'There is no point in winning, if you are not winning fair'.\", \"from\": 5952, \"to\": 6071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think you know that truth in your heart.\", \"from\": 6072, \"to\": 6114, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you touch and you know you are cheating, you are not winning.\", \"from\": 6115, \"to\": 6179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For me, if you have been on that and have been contaminated twice, as an honourable person, you should be out of the sport.\", \"from\": 6181, \"to\": 6305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we know sport is not that simple.\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have also been asked about people who have not been contaminated and I respect that.\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not want to paint a whole nation or a whole group of people with one brush, that would be very unfair.\\\"\", \"from\": 6432, \"to\": 6541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's Kishane Thompson wins the third semi-final in 9.80 and reinforces his status as gold medal favourite.\", \"from\": 6543, \"to\": 6654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6543, \"end\": 6550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9543409086646387e-21, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 6561, \"end\": 6569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999956736931288, \"rank\": 4.326325867407299e-06, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coincidentally, that is the same time as Marcell Jacobs ran to win gold in 2021 - and the Italian will have a chance to do it again after qualifying by 0.03 seconds.\", \"from\": 6656, \"to\": 6821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6697, \"end\": 6711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zharnel Hughes finishes 14th overall having run 10.01 seconds.\", \"from\": 6823, \"to\": 6885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6831, \"end\": 6837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9999999997762643, \"rank\": 2.1359946729428933e-10, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has still not been under 10 seconds in what has been an injury-troubled season.\", \"from\": 6886, \"to\": 6968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No luck for Louie Hinchliffe in the second semi-final.\", \"from\": 6970, \"to\": 7024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6982, \"end\": 6987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\", \"score\": 0.9999999738156479, \"rank\": 2.6184373209320623e-08, \"text\": \"Louie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Akani Simbine of South Africa and Botswana's Letsile Simbine are through automatically, while defending champion Marcell Jacobs and Kenny Bednarek are now \\\"in the hot seat\\\" of the losers' places.\", \"from\": 7025, \"to\": 7220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7025, \"end\": 7038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}, {\"begin\": 7042, \"end\": 7054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.672366902392702e-14, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 7059, \"end\": 7067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 9.415756334214487e-11, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 7138, \"end\": 7152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}, {\"begin\": 7157, \"end\": 7171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They ran 9.92 and 9.93 respectively.\", \"from\": 7221, \"to\": 7257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zharnel Hughes, up next, is Britain's last remaining hope of ending a 32-year streak without a medal in the men's 100m.\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7267, \"end\": 7273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9999999997762643, \"rank\": 2.1359946729428933e-10, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}, {\"begin\": 7287, \"end\": 7294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9766561376943033, \"rank\": 0.02390182317506514, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile at the swimming, Team GB have finished fourth in the 4x100m medley relay - and Adam Peaty has said afterwards that he will be taking another break from the sport.\", \"from\": 7380, \"to\": 7552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7407, \"end\": 7414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.963415818533111e-14, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 7443, \"end\": 7462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.14069432262704e-14, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7469, \"end\": 7479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tomorrow is never promised and if my heart wants it my heart wants it and I will sign that contract with myself to do it,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7554, \"to\": 7686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That could be a long way away, but I think I have got to step away from the sport because it hurt too much this time.\", \"from\": 7688, \"to\": 7806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am going to take some time off everything and I do not really know what the answer is.\", \"from\": 7808, \"to\": 7897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am taking time, if my family needs me they need me.\", \"from\": 7898, \"to\": 7951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know you can not lie to your heart but if it wants it, it wants it.\\\"\", \"from\": 7952, \"to\": 8029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not adjust your TV sets, that really is what Louie Hinchliffe's hair looks like.\", \"from\": 8031, \"to\": 8114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8079, \"end\": 8084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\", \"score\": 0.9999999738156479, \"rank\": 2.6184373209320623e-08, \"text\": \"Louie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pikmin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The man with the mullet is the hottest British sprinting sensation, was a junior golfer until he was 17 and has now switched to athletics and is coached by the great Carl Lewis.\", \"from\": 8116, \"to\": 8293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8155, \"end\": 8162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9150977042968397, \"rank\": 0.0918917956708962, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 8282, \"end\": 8292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is Great Britain's first of two semi-finalists, sandwiched between USA's Noah Lyles and Jamaica's Oblique Seville.\", \"from\": 8295, \"to\": 8412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8365, \"end\": 8368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.474035094038322, \"rank\": 0.7119644634354305, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 8371, \"end\": 8381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 8386, \"end\": 8393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9543409086646387e-21, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 8404, \"end\": 8411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3433646308404947e-21, \"text\": \"Seville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Third for Hinchliffe in 9.97 seconds, only 0.02 secs outside his personal best.\", \"from\": 8414, \"to\": 8493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles is beaten again: it was Hinchliffe in the heats and it was Seville of Jamaica this time, who ran a personal best of 9.81.\", \"from\": 8495, \"to\": 8622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were no Jamaicans in the final three years ago, but there will be at least one this time.\", \"from\": 8624, \"to\": 8719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8638, \"end\": 8647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8000751928897663e-29, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hinchliffe, by the way, is now waiting on a fastest loser's spot, of which there are two.\", \"from\": 8721, \"to\": 8810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be praying for a slow semi-final to follow\\u2026  Adam Peaty was unable to inspire Team GB to a podium place as they finished fourth in the men's 4\\u00d7100m medley relay final.\", \"from\": 8811, \"to\": 8986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8864, \"end\": 8874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 8897, \"end\": 8904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.963415818533111e-14, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Peaty, who on Saturday described how he had had the \\\"worst week\\\" of his life physically after testing positive for Covid on Monday, left Team GB second at halfway, they fell away thereafter.\", \"from\": 8988, \"to\": 9184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9131, \"end\": 9138, \"title\": \"http: